@description.name: @description
@description.body: Model providers bridge user-provided data functionality with Qookery interfaces

@description.name: @description
@description.body:
Return a JavaScript primitive or array of primitives that uniquely identifies model object

The result must be such so that if a == b, then identityOf(a) == identityOf(b) and vice-versa.

The result must be null when no input was passed.

@param.name: @param
@param.body: object {any} model object - it may be null

@return.name: @return
@return.body: {any} any JavaScript primitive or array of primitives
@return.description: any JavaScript primitive or array of primitives

@description.name: @description
@description.body:
Test two model objects for equality

Method must be null-safe: equals(null, null) -> true and equals(null, non-null) -> false

@return.name: @return
@return.body: {Boolean} true if objects are equal or both null
@return.description: true if objects are equal or both null

@description.name: @description
@description.body:
Returns a negative number, zero, or a positive number as object1 is less than, equal to, or greater than object2

Method must be null-safe: compare(null, null) -> 0, compare(null, non-null) -> -1 and compare(non-null, null) -> 1

@return.name: @return
@return.body: {Number} negative number, positive number or zero according to comparison result
@return.description: negative number, positive number or zero according to comparison result

@description.name: @description
@description.body:
Convert values from component specific to model objects

Provider is expected to convert given component specific value to a model object.

@param.name: @param
@param.body: className {String} the name of the value's class
@param.description: the name of the value's class

@return.name: @return
@return.body: {any} value if no conversion needed, conversion result, or null if conversion was attempted but failed
@return.description: value if no conversion needed, conversion result, or null if conversion was attempted but failed

@description.name: @description
@description.body:
Convert values from model objects to component specific values

Provider is expected to convert given model object into an object of the required class for component specific needs.

@param.name: @param
@param.body: className {String} the name of the wanted value's class
@param.description: the name of the wanted value's class

@return.name: @return
@return.body: {any} input if no conversion needed, conversion result, or null if conversion was attempted but failed
@return.description: input if no conversion needed, conversion result, or null if conversion was attempted but failed

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Return a human-friendly label for a model object

@param.name: @param
@param.body: object {any} model object - it may not be null
@param.description: model object - it may not be null

@param.name: @param
@param.body: labelType {String?} optional symbolic name of needed label type
@param.description: optional symbolic name of needed label type

@return.name: @return
@return.body: {String} any textual label or null if none available
@return.description: any textual label or null if none available

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Connect a component to the form's underlying model, in a way specified by second argument

@param.name: @param
@param.body: component {qookery.IEditableComponent} editable component that will receive connection
@param.description: editable component that will receive connection

@param.name: @param
@param.body: specification {String} an implementation specific text that will be parsed by the model provider
@param.description: an implementation specific text that will be parsed by the model provider
